TestNG - Test Driven Development
---------------------------------
Test cases - Excel

Advantages / Features:
--------------------- 
TestNG will generate default html report. (test-output)
we can set priorities in test cases (Test case level)
we can group the test cases easily
data provider is possible in testNG
we can pass parameters to our test scripts.
parallel and crossbrowser execution is possible in testng.
we can rerun the failure test cases automatically.

Annotations:
-----------
@BeforeSuite
@BeforeClass
@BeforeMethod
@BeforeGroup
@BeforeTest
@Test
@AfterTest
@AfterGroup
@AfterMethod
@AfterClass
@AfterSuite
@DataProvider
@Parameter

Execution Order:
---------------
@BeforeClass
@BeforeMethod
@Test
@AfterMethod
@AfterClass

Test Level
-----------
Priority
group
invocation count
enabled

Assert:
-------
Hard & Soft

AssertTrue
AssertEquals

To Rerun failure test cases:
----------------------------
2 Interface
IRetryAnalyzer (retry) ----> It is for Known failure test cases
IAnnotationTransformer (transform) ----> It is for unknown test cases
